<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-02T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-02T07:00:00-05:00" n="726" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d726">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.632/104: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stockton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-02T13:00:00+01:00">April 2, 1931—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 1:30 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>26. Department’s 15, April 1, 1 p.m. Foreign Office has just informed me
                            officially Austrian President ratified supplemental article and <pb facs="0977" n="863" xml:id="pg_863"/> reservation March 28th.
                            Necessary countersignatures of Chancellor, Minister for Foreign Affairs,
                            and Minister of Commerce have since been affixed and Austria is now
                            ready to effect exchange. Urge President’s ratification be
                            expedited.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stockton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>